/* Routes for navigation within the SPA */
/* All requests that don't match a static file are redirected to index.html */
/* This is required for standard react-router configuration on Cloudflare Pages */

/*
  https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/routing/
*/

/* Catch-all route */
/*   Source      Destination   Status */
/*   -------------------------------- */
/*   /*          /index.html   200    */

/* NOTE: Cloudflare uses a _redirects file or a functions-based fallback. */
/* For static pages, the most reliable way is often a simple 200 rule. */

/* The following line informs Cloudflare to serve index.html for all non-file paths */
/* (This applies if you're not using Cloudflare Workers for routing) */
/* Actually, for Cloudflare Pages, just having index.html and no server usually works, */
/* but explicitly adding this helps with deep linking. */

/* Rules: */
/* /* /index.html 200 */
